  "id": "BIT-mongodb-2026-8202",
  "summary": "Post-authentication CPU utilization DoS via $trim/$ltrim/$rtrim operators",
  "details": "Using a densely populated chars mask and a large input string in the MongoDB aggregation operators $trim, $ltrim, and $rtrim, an authenticated user with aggregation permissions can pin CPU utilization at 100% for an extended period of time.\n\nThis issue impacts MongoDB Server v7.0 versions prior to 7.0.34, v8.0 versions prior to 8.0.23, v8.2 versions prior to 8.2.9 and v8.3 versions prior to 8.3.2.",
  "aliases": [
    "CVE-2026-8202"
